text: María Eugenia Rojas (born 27 December 1977) is a Peruvian former professional tennis player. Rojas competed on the professional tour in the 1990s and reached a best singles ranking of 504 in the world. Between 1995 and 1998, Rojas represented the Peru Fed Cup team in a total of 13 ties, winning six singles and five doubles matches.
